      • onSessionManagerExit

        public void onSessionManagerExit(Object cause)
        Called prior to SessionManager exit.

        Default implementation is to try to re-establish a logged on session unless we are outside our scheduled times in which case we do not restart manager processing.

        If we are inside our scheduled times, default behaviour is to log an error message to the effect that we have lost our session when it is scheduled to be active. Then it will restart the manager processing to try to re-stablish the session. This is done in different ways depending on the cause parameter.

        • if cause is a LoggedOnStatusEvent calls onSessionManagerLogoutExit(com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.event.LoggedOnStatusEvent).
        • if cause is a DisconnectRequestedEvent of type ISessionManager.TERMINATION_CODE_MyLogout - Will stop retrying to log on.
        • if cause is anything else, including null - Will create a new session and new connection and retry logging on.
        Specified by:
        onSessionManagerExit in interface IClientConnectionManager
        Parameters:
        cause - Object which caused exit.
